https://multimodal-ai-research-assistant.vercel.app/

“This project focuses on building an intelligent system that

can read multiple PDF documents and answer user

questions based on their content. The system uses Natural

Language Processing (NLP) and Large Language Models

(LLMs) to provide accurate and context-based answers

read research papers(PDF) extract figures , tables math

answer question using tech stack

LLM(llama/OpenAI/Gemini), PDF parsing, summarization,

dashboard UI. The main goal of this project is to automate information

retrieval from PDFs and improve the efficiency of

searching and understanding large documents. A full-stack research assistant with a ChatGPT-style

frontend and a FastAPI backend for PDF-grounded

question answering using Retrieval-Augmented Generation

(RAG). https://multimodal-ai-research-assistant.vercel.app/
Mention the work done by each member :

1. Rupesh Kumar Thakur(ME):

Led the frontend development and assisted in deployment and

hosting-related tasks. I also participated in system testing and

interface improvements during the mid-semester phase. 2. Swetankan Kumar Sinha :

led the backend development and system integration. His

work includes the design and implementation of the RAG

pipeline, FastAPI backend development, vector database

integration using FAISS, and overall system coordination. He

also contributed to frontend-backend integration and technical

documentation. 3. Purushottam Kumar Singh :

Developed an initial prototype based on LangChain for PDF- based question answering, which helped in early-stage idea

validation. He also contributed to the frontend development

and assisted in refining the user interface of the current system. 4. Anurag Kumar Thakur :

contributed to frontend support and testing of the system. He

was involved in reviewing system behavior, identifying issues,

and assisting in improving usability. 5. Shivam Kumar Singh :

He has neither actively contributed to the current

implementation phase of the project nor participated in any

meeting held for discussion of the project
